When developing more complicated user interfaces with a plugin, chances are some CSS will be required.

Right now, the best way to include said CSS seems to be including a `<style>` tag in the template file. While this works, it would be nice to be able to specify a `styles` dict on the challenge class similar to templates. This stylesheet would be added to the page in the same way as the templates/scripts already are (well, as the templates are, the scripts don't have a cachebusting parameter added to their URL, which gets in the way sometimes)

```python
class MyChallenge(BaseChallenge):
    id = "test2"
    name = "test2"
    templates = {
        "create": "/plugins/test_challenge/assets/create.html",
        "update": "/plugins/test_challenge/assets/update.html",
        "view": "/plugins/test_challenge/assets/view.html",
    }
    scripts = {
        "create": "/plugins/test_challenge/assets/create.js",
        "update": "/plugins/test_challenge/assets/update.js",
        "view": "/plugins/test_challenge/assets/view.js",
    }
    styles = {
        "create": "/plugins/test_challenge/assets/create.css",
    }

```

