comment.body:
I would probably describe this pattern with something like:

```ts
/**
 * May be listened to with `app.listen(player, "<method name>", <method>)`
 */
export interface PlayerEvents {
  playbackState(newState: string): void
  nowPlayingModified(): void
}
```

This has the advantage of also providing types, so I could do `const listener: PlayerEvents["playbackState"]`, and later pass that to the listen method. Your `app.listen` method could then also be typed with something like:

```ts
interface PlayerEvents {
  playbackState(newState: string): void
  nowPlayingModified(): void
}
interface Player { isPlayer: true }

interface TrackEvents {
    complete(): void;
}
interface Track { isTrack: true }

interface App {
    // could do this without overloads, but this keeps types pretty simple
    listen<K extends keyof PlayerEvents>(obj: Player, event: K, callback: PlayerEvents[K]): void
    listen<K extends keyof TrackEvents>(obj: Track, event: K, callback: TrackEvents[K]): void
}
```

